<review>One of the best hair salon's in Los Angeles!!!  I highly recommend Hairzoo. This place is incredible. From the friendly staff that greets you when you walk in the door, to the super talented stylist that gives you exactly what you want, all for an incredible value. Hairzoo is simply awesome!

I'm a clean-cut guy that likes to get my hair done every two weeks. Growing up in LA, I've experienced my fair share of hair salons. This place is numero uno! The environment is comfortable, hip, and relaxing. (It isn't like those other barbershops with the lame posters from the 1980's rock bands everywhere.) Hairzoo has a beautifully decorated interior, great lighting, and really comfortable chairs.

All the hairstylist are super talented and friendly. They listen to your wants, discuss various options, and work with you to get you the perfect look. I was very impressed the first time I had my hair done at Hairzoo. Never have I looked this good.

Also the pricing is wonderful! Far too many salons in LA completely rip people off charging $60 - $70 for a single haircut!  Hairzoo on the other hand offers talented stylists, in a comfortable environment, all for an affordable price. Finally a hair salon that is worth it! I'm so happy Hairzoo opened up here in L.A. Life just got a lot better...</review>< Rate>

<userid>112094274608446645330<//userid><Name>Brian Van Etten<//Name>< Text>
Terry is a beast. I contacted him for my first tattoo and he made the whole process so comfortable and smooth. If you choose Terry as your artist (congrats for the smart decision) expect the process to go something like this:
1. Send email or call shop about idea and location of tattoo.
2. Put down your deposit to reserve your dates. He is usually booked at least 6 months out.
3. His assistant will confirm and book all sessions in advance with you. Each session will be at least two weeks apart. Full sleeve for example is 8 sessions. Keep that in mind for traveling/holidays, it takes awhile.
4. During your first appointment, Terry will draw the whole tattoo right in front of you. It‚Äôs awesome.
5. Watch Terry make your natural skin color disappear at mind bending speeds.
Remington is a shop full of awesome artists and they are all super friendly. This shop isn‚Äôt for those wanting a design they found on Pinterest traced on their skin. Not that they wouldn‚Äôt do it, but the artists here can all draw and you pay for what you get. Let them draw you something custom no one else will have, you won‚Äôt regret it.< /Text>

< Review>
Remington Tattoo Parlor - My artist was Terry Ribera.

let me start off by saying, i got a tattoo cover up done by Terry.

Before even finding Terry and Remington Tattoo, i contacted SEVERAL tattoo artists to see if they could get the job done, what my options were and had many questions about the process in general.. Many emails going unresponsive - never hearing from them, or when the few artists finally did respond (took several weeks), pretty much every artist told me a cover up would not be possible and i would need to do laser removal first. No one wanted to work with me. At that point i had lost hope that this was ever going to be possible.

Then comes my experience with Terry. Frustrated and a little upset that no one wanted to work with me, i had googled something like 'best cover up tattoo artist', seeing as i need to find someone who has a lot of experience with covering tattoos. Google referred me to Remington Tattoo... i looked through Terry's portfolio, loved the art and his work, and i read that the shop specializes in things like this... so i said, ok, lets send a message. This is probably the last bit of hope i had left.

i believe it was literally 1 day later. i received a really lengthy, well composed, very informative and detailed response from Terry. Not only saying he would have no problem doing the cover up, but also went into such detail about the process. Like, deep into the technical details of why he would do XYZ when doing the cover, going into black&grey theory, etc!. I was shocked... every other artist wasn't giving me the time of day, and the various vague responses i got all told me to just laser it off first. Here comes Terry, with this extremely personal, detailed, lengthy  email message, you could immediately tell "this guy loves his job". He took time out of his day to really make me feel comfortable. i didn't hear from an assistance just telling me to come in. He took his personal time, which essentially is what won me over.

And every experience after that was just as professional and great. We met up for the consultation, pre-covid, so he can take a look at my existing tattoo. In person, he was extremely personable, it felt like i was hanging out with an old friend. He was super confident. I brought some example images i found on google for brainstorming and idea sharing. He immediately began drawing right in front of me and came up with a really wicked tattoo idea which i was extremely happy about. Went home that night feeling not like just another customer at a tattoo shop, but as if i had made a friend.

it took us 2 sessions, about 6 hours, Terry works extremely fast and efficient. He gets the ink in and gets you out there, no fooling around. i left with an awesome tattoo, that is a very unique style, and honestly, couldnt have been happier with the overall experience. I have had other tattoo's done before, and i can say, this experience was not like any other. This was the most comfortable and positive experience i have ever had in a tatttoo chair. Even after leaving, and being done, a few texts messages of Terry sharing pictures of the final product and his sincerity about having me as a client... it went a long way in my book... considering, for me, the communication was superb from the very first email, you can tell it was genuine.

the shop was extremely clean, everyone was very nice and professional, and there's really not a bad thing i could say about the shop.... well, other than the drive. I live in Orange County, and going to San Diego was a bit of a trek... but not too bad, that is not the shops fault.

10/10, would recommend Remington and Terry 100%. great experience, great vibes and i will be going back to get more when time, money  and ideas of what to do next allows... Thank you Terry.

-Andy K from OC</Review>

I anticipated full well ahead of time Terry would be a busy artist with appointments booked well in advance throughout the year for large pieces but I knew any wait would be worth it. I brought with me a mere concept in mind to commemorate 10 years since a significant incident happened in my life. As Terry began to draw from scratch and bring my concept to life I knew I was in the right place. The draft of what would eventually morph later into a final product was drawn that day and I had full confidence Terry would later execute the full piece with expert precision. Now I just had to wait until July 2019 for my 1st appointment. As the days drew near Terry completed the final drawing, which I received via email, and I was both blown away and excited to begin. Six sessions later between July and October 2019 , consisting of between 2-3 hours each, and I was proud to display a full Terry Ribera original piece of art. A minor 15-min touch up session at the end of November followed and I again knew I had chosen the right artist. Terry‚Äôs vision for every piece he executes is second to none. Terry is just an all around excellent human being and I was lucky to have been able to work with him. The overall atmosphere of the shop was fantastic during each session as everyone was very friendly, professional and just great to be around. <review>This is a decent older park. It has tad bark vs. a rubbery ground cover. It has two regular swings, two baby swings. The play structure is best suited for kids 4-5 +. My daughter is almost 2 and she can manage the stairs to the main slides, which are steep, but she's brave. Some other features she just too little for. There's a small slide but it has a rough texture so you don't really slide on it. This is my closest park, so we go here when we are short on time. There is lots of open space around the play area with nice picnic tables. There's no bathrooms. It's clean and kept up.</review><Date>1612969503924</Date>< Resp>

<text>I have been a customer of honeybaked since I can remember and I‚Äôve eaten their food since I was a child. The fact that they will not make you a sandwich during a ‚Äúholiday‚Äú is disappointing, especially when the store is empty.  As someone who does not celebrate Easter, I didn‚Äôt even know what holiday was coming. It‚Äôs Monday. The ‚Äúholiday‚Äù it‚Äôs not until Sunday. I understand when things are busy and in a crunch how this is necessary and I would not be writing this in that situation; however there were five people behind the counter and someone at the sandwich counter doing nothing. There was one other person pre-ordering a ham. As a frequent customer, there was absolutely no reason to not make me a sandwich. It‚Äôs important for a business to be willing to alter rules when there‚Äôs clearly the ability to do so. I respect everyone who celebrates Easter however the equal respect should be given to those who do not. <Review>We have liked Honey Baked Hams for many years and usually will have one or two of them each year.  This year we bought a small one for our Christmas dinner.  It was small because we are keeping our distance during the pandemic.

To get a ham, you will need to order it ahead of time.  To pick it up, the order will stay when it will be available.  we arrived at this place about 2:00 PM on Tuesday and the line to get in the store showed there were about six people in line.  The store is small, and there are other things like deserts available, so the browsing of the people tends to make the line slower than it might be at a less busy time.

Our wait to get took about twenty-minutes to go from waiting in line to placing the ham in the trunk.  Tomorrow, we'll have the ham and it would surprise me if it wasn't just as perfect as we are expecting.

This is small, but nice store.  The people are helpful and pleasant.< /Review>< response>
None< /response>

< Review>
Every year, I usually order 5-6 medium sized ham (Encinitas store) and will gift them to relatives. This year, I have pre-ordered and picked up in store (Encinitas) total of 6 medium half boned ham for Thanksgiving and Christmas. This time, my relatives and I noticed that they are not the same honey baked ham we used to love. The hams were not the Golden Baked sugared ham we used to get in the past. This ham looks old, like a much cheaper, had been frozen, store-bought ham, dark like oven burned, and not what the store advertised as Golden Honey Baked Ham that we used to love. Very disappointed and not worth the money spent. I may not consider buying them again for my family and will definitely not buy for gifting to my relatives during the holidays. Please bring back the real Honey Baked Ham that the store is well known for.<//Review>

<UserId.>113255244479304148687< /UserId.><Pics>None</Pics>< text>
Dan H just came and replaced my defective sliding door. He did a great job, the door looks and works great.
My issue with this company is the lack of  Communication with me the customer. The first door they installed was defective and they tried to repair it once. It was decided the door needed to be replaced. Everything was good up to this point. I did not get a call with a timeline on how long this would take. So when I called to see what was happening and to complain  about the lack of communication. I was told a manager or possibly the owner would give me a call back with an explanation. I was never called back. After several weeks went bye I called back I was told I was going to get a  partial refund for my trouble. Had Dan H. out to look at our ten year old Renewal by Andersen windows. The windows (which have performed great since their installation) are showing some signs of aesthetic wear on the rails (primarily due to intense sun exposure on that side of the house). He was very friendly and helpful - giving explanations of what causes wear and tear, and how to maintain the windows for maximum durability. <user>111466767021440654034<//user><username>Janice Lightfoot< /username><Date>1571241914613< /Date>< rating>
5<//rating>
< Review>
Our journey with Renewal by Andersen (RBA) started when we decided to replace some old windows.  We have pretty good quality windows throughout the house, except for the living room (previous owner went over reno budget and stopped the project).  Not knowing we have RBA windows, we called other companies that offered vinyl replacement, after viewed their product (we were told we have vinyl windows in the house), we are still not convinced the "vinyl" windows are what we already have in the house.  Then my husband just happened to look at the corner of our daughter's bathroom window and found a mark indicated " Andersen"...  So, we jumped on Google and searched Andersen windows and found RBA Windows.

Called RBA windows, got to see and feel their samples (which felt like the same stuff we already have in the house).  After the sales lady checked our windows and told us that we actually have RBA Windows.  So, even though RBA's quote was much higher than the others we have gotten, but my husband and I felt that it's best to match the rest of the house with the same quality windows, and we are very glad we did.

During measuring appointment, I noticed the weather stip on couple of our older windows (came with the house when we bought it) came out of the track.  Sales lady called on our behalf and started the repair ordr ticket to have those replaced, under warranty!

Throughout the entire process from ordering parts to setting appointment to having the repair technician come out, was exceptional!
On the day of our repair appointment, repair technician Dan H. came well within our appointment time frame and started the work.  He was very polite, his work was very proficient and got the windows repaired very quickly.

My husband and I couldn't be happier with our decision to go with RBA Windows, we definitely got what paid for and more with not only the quality product, but exceptional customer service!!  We highly recommend RBA Windows to anyone who is looking to replace their windows!<//Review>

< review>
We recently installed a sliding door and a dining room window. As we researched products, Jeff from Renewal came to our home and spent quite a bit of time explaining their product.  There are monetary incentives for ordering from him immediately.We do not make rash decisions.  He did give us until the end of the day but after talking to a salesperson from another company, we realized we would go with Renewal.
Because the windows are custom, there is a waiting period of a few weeks while the windows are constructed. But they finished ours a little early and we were delighted.Throughout the waiting period Renewal
stayed in touch with us by phone. The ladies that perform this service are
very competent and kind.
On the day of installation, Audy A. and Lupe V. arrived promptly and began work immediately. They work together well and were very professional and friendly. Although they were very efficient, they did not
rush the project. The job did take all day but we were happy with that
because they did not have to come back. They did it right the first time!
Fernando came a few days later and did a very efficient touch up with paint. He arrived within the time the schedulers said he would and
was friendly.
Andy, Lupe and Fernando all did such a wonderful cleanup job and left no signs that they had been there.
Although Renewal is more pricey then many window companies, we feel
we got our money's worth.  The professionals that we dealt with were
a step above other companies and the product is superior. It is 100 degrees in our backyard right now but when you put your hand to the
glass, it is cool to the touch.</review>

<Pics>None</Pics><UserId.>115059167609609622987<//UserId.><resp>{'time': 1512144905885, 'text': 'John, you deserve the red carpet service. We appreciate the wonderful feedback and never hesitate too call if you ever need anything!'}< /resp>< Review>
As I've come to expect from this company, my latest experience was great. I asked if two of my Renewal by Anderson window screens could be replaced since they were corroding at the edge where the stainless screening material mated with the aluminum frame. They asked for a couple pictures and ordered the screens.

When they called to say the screens were in, I fully expected they'd have me stop by to pick them up. Nope, they said they'd deliver them.

Dan H. came by and installed them. He even called to say he was running early and would it be OK to stop by 45 minutes earlier than the appointment time.

The one thing I would suggest is to await a promotion with a straight percentage discount. I made the mistake of contracting when they offered a certain number of free windows based on the total number ordered. Since the free ones are the cheapest ones, I chose to leave out the one really small bathroom window to get a more expensive window free. I planned to buy that one window later but didn't realize the installation price for a single window makes that an expensive option. Yes, I shot myself in the foot and now sit with one non-matching window.

Update: After eight years, the need arose to have all of the weatherstripping replaced. No problem. RBA came and installed all new weatherstripping. John G did a great job and worked his tail off.</Review>

Oscar Gomez, Lead person showed up with Alan Robinson at the appointed time, went over all the work they were going to perform, then they laid down the protective covering for the carpet and hard surface areas, then the rest of the crew of Christian Viera, and Oscar Castro showed up, they proceeded to discuss what and by whom the work was going to be done and proceeded to perform the work. I told them I was a retired Carpenter Working Supervisor, and that unless I got in their way I was going to do what little I could do, Oscar Gomez had no problem, so I proceeded.

I admired the working relationship they have and it was a wonderful and joyous experience I had, they all acted with great respect for myself and my wife, they treated our home as though it was their own.

I told Oscar Gomez that no one works at out home without my wife and I providing them with lunch!

They agreed, and Alan Robinson wanted to  get his lunch at Puffy Taco as he remembered it when he was a kid, so my wife got a menu and they all picked what they wanted and we went 30 minutes before they broke for lunch, got them their food, brought it home, laid their food on the dinner table, told them to get their drinks from the refrigerator and they had a very pleasant lunch and were very grateful for the kindness my wife and I showed them.

Oscar Gomez discovered that they were not in possession of all that was needed, he called the shop to see if it was there, and discovered that the item was not shipped, they apologized and explained what had happened, we understood and stated that it was not a problem.

When they were done with the installation, they cleaned up the inside of the house where they had worked as well as the outside, my wife gave them some cookies for their afternoon break.

Oscar Gomez took my wife and I through a walk through on all 6 windows and the sliding door demonstrating how they work, we were very satisfied with their work, their respect of my wife and I and the feeling of friendship that was fostered during the job.

We highly recommend Renewal by Anderson, they product is great, and their employees to perform the installation are great themselves.<//review>

< Review>
Last week I had 2 sliding glass doors and 2 windows installed by Renewal by Andersen. I am very satisfied! From the initial sales presentation with Carlos, to the measuring appointment with Omar, and the two-day seamless installation process with Christian A., Refugio, and Valentin, I have only praise and satisfaction for this company. Everything proceeded as promised. Omar was exceedingly meticulous with his measurements, which was important because I have expensive plantation shutters that I did not want removed or damaged in any way. Christian and his crew took extra good care of my home and furnishings when having to remove stucco from around the sliding glass doors. All of my belongings were carefully covered and protected from the messy dust, and my hardwood floors were protected with carpets. Chris, Cuco, and Valentin were professional, respectful, highly competent, and very pleasant to be around.

That said, RBA is high-end. The price is considerable. But there are some things you don't want to go cheap on. Quality doors and windows are a sound investment for any home. I feel I made the right decision going with RBA.</Review>

I had Anderson Renewal install all new windows and doors in my house over 13 years ago. The three 12-foot wide windows were leaking badly and I had one window that was broken due to a painter's mishap. I placed a service call and even though my windows were old they were very professional and sent someone out to assess the problem. Dan H., the technician, came out twice to fix the leaks and the broken window. Dan caulked all the windows on the outside of the house and that completely stopped the leaks. The water intrusion was caused not by the windows, but by the stucco pulling away from the casing. Renewal is all about stopping the leaks and subsequent damage. While Dan was there he also fixed one of my doors which was sticking badly. He did this on his own as he saw it was not functioning properly. Dan also installed a new door handle and expertly fixed the broken window. I have had a lot of contractors at my home and Dan is at top of the list. He is fast, expert at his craft, and a really nice guy. He also lets you know if he is running late. Very professional service all the way around from Renewal by Anderson. <Text>We are very happy with our new windows, French Door and Gliding Patio Door from Renewal By Andersen of Orange County.  It all started with a pleasant trip to their showroom in Laguna Hills.  Lisa was so nice, accommodating and informative and was a BIG part in our decision to consider Renewal By Anderson.  We ended up calling the phone number and got routed to Andersen's central call center.  This was the only bad experience we had.  The call center was rude and did not even want to set up an appointment since we were going through an insurance claim on our kitchen due to a water slab leak.  I explained to them that the windows had nothing to do with the insurance and we wanted to take the opportunity to upgrade our windows while the kitchen was being worked on.  I was totally frustrated with their call center and almost didn't book an appointment and told them if they don't want my business, I'll install Milgard windows.  (Hint: When you call for an appointment, try to call the Laguna Hills office directly).  Enough about the Call Center (making my blood boil).  Sean M was the sales guys from Andersen who came by and he was very pleasant and knowledgeable and went through all of our options.  We really enjoyed Sean.  We ended up purchasing six windows and a French Door and actually later added a Gliding Patio Door as well.  Vicente M and Bernardo S and the crew installed the windows and doors and were very professional.  They worked very hard and their workmanship was top notch.  You can tell they knew their product.  After the work was completed, they cleaned up everything nicely.  They were very conscientious in their work.  Yes, it was expensive, but you can tell we got a very high quality product.  We love the secure locking mechanism on the doors.  We highly recommend Renewal By Andersen of Orange County.< /Text>< pics>

<Text>I would like to give my review on my new Renewal by Anderson doors and windows!  I rarely give a five star rating to anything because I have a thing about nothing being perfect!  Well my experience with the Renewal team has made my list! We were shopping for six Windows, two patio doors and a new front door.  We have read a lot of reviews, asked family and friends, also our neighbors about their recent window purchases! Some were really good and some not so good.  The common among all of them was that they all had vinyl Windows installed!   I have nothing against vinyl Windows, heck I sold them myself.  But I you want a quality custom retrofit window, Renewal by Anderson is the way to go!  It started with our Sales Consultant Carlos Jimenez.   He showed up on time,  took a rough measurements of our doors and windows, gave us our pricing options.  We made our decision on the spot!  A few days later Mr Jimenez had a thank you card and a beautiful flower arrangement sent to our house! We were scheduled for our official measurements a week later with Job Technician Mike Booker.  Very professional, went over and with great detail confirmed everything!   On August 25, 26 and 27th was our install date.  8:30am on the 25th (on time and on the right date) our install team rang our door bell.  Christian A., Joseph P and Joel introduced themselves.  Neat, clean each day.  All you can ask for.  By day 3 everything was completed and ready for our touch up appointment!  I will review that when it happens! All in all, my wife and I are completely satisfied with the entire Renewal Orange County team!  The do it  right!  Follow up calls, appointment calls and especially our thank you card and Cookies (yes cookies) from the owner Charlie Gindele himself!
Thank you,
Mr. and Mrs. Gonzales

<userid>118319457035364979447< /userid><name>Sid Sawal< /name><time>1475787579027</time><Rate>5<//Rate><Review>I recently had my windows, patio sliding door and front entrance door replaced by Renewal by Anderson.  I have heard that they are not your typical windows installer but I was pleasant surprised by the service I received from them.
I got introduced to them via door to door salesmen that were in uniform and were extremely polite with some knowledge of the product.  I decided to set up an appointment with their Design Consultant.  Renewal by Anderson office called to remind me of my appointment.  My design consultant, Daniel Mecham was on time and spent plenty of time explaining the difference between Renewal by Anderson windows vs. the popular vinyl windows.  It appeared to be more than just another sales pitch since I have had really bad experience with vinyl windows at my previous house so I was willing to pay a little extra to get better quality.  Daniel worked with me to get all credit approvals and provide me with details to turn in to HOA for approval as well.
Once I received the HOA approval, Renewal by Anderson sent over the Job Technician, Dennis Rohrbach, who did a real through job in measuring the windows. Once the measurements were taken, it was discovered by the HQ installation Manager, Michael Wherry that one of the windows might not work the way the Design Consultant had explained. Michael along with the Sales Manager, Joey Obledo came to my house to explain how the windows along with the front entrance door we had bought will not work as designed and presented me with different options.  We ended up picking one of the options. This is an exceptional customer service that I had not experienced in a very long time.
The installation team showed on time to start the installation, it took them three days to install and one day to finish up the trimming.  All furniture was put back for me to use at night if it was moved during the day time. They cleaned every day and were considered of my neighbors. The installation team was made up of Project Manager Casey and associates, Jose, Oscar, Freddie, Omar, Bernardo, Joseph, Josh and Dan Hernandez.  The trim guys were Marco and Frank.  I would like to whole heartedly thank them for their awesome job and professionalism.
I know this review is longer then what I am use to writing but this is a great company with great employees and they have not forgotten about customer service. Not to sound like a clich√© but surely you get what you pay for with this company. I would like to highly recommend them to anyone looking to replace their windows, sliding door and front entrance doors.<//Review>< Pics>
